{"id":"resp_01kx654tycfrjrc2vg1bh653zt","object":"response","status":"completed","created_at":1783691897,"output":[{"type":"reasoning","id":"resp_01kx654tycfrkb8fssbz74s6bc","status":"completed","content":[{"type":"reasoning_text","text":"The user says: \"noo i am sad gng\". Possibly they typed incorrectly: \"nooo i am sad gng\". The user expresses sadness. They might want support. We need to respond empathetically. Provide supportive response, ask how they're feeling, encourage them. Possibly suggest coping strategies or resources. Also note that they might be in crisis: we can encourage them to reach out to a trusted person, call suicide helpline if needed. Provide resources for suicide prevention lines. Provide supportive, non-judgmental. So answer: I'm sorry to hear that. How can I help? Encourage them to talk, maybe some suggestions. Also check if they have immediate risk. The user might be a minor or adult? We don't know. We can give general guidelines: if feeling suicidal, call 988 (US) or local helpline. Encourage to talk to friend, mental health professional. Provide supportive language. So respond accordingly."}],"summary":[]},{"type":"message","id":"msg_01kx654tycfrkt02xrntkhna4x","status":"completed","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"output_text","text":"I’m really sorry you’re feeling this way. It sounds like you’re going through a tough time right now. I’m here to listen and help if I can.\n\n---\n\n### How you’re feeling  \n- Are you feeling *sad* because of something specific (a breakup, work, family, etc.)?  \n- Do you feel *overwhelmed* or *hopeless*?  \n- Are you having thoughts of harming yourself or feeling like you might act on those thoughts?\n\nKnowing a bit more can help me give you better support. If you’re comfortable sharing, I’d love to hear more. If you’re not ready to talk, that’s okay too—just let me know how you’d like to proceed.\n\n---\n\n### Immediate steps you can try\n\n| What you can do | Why it helps |\n|-----------------|--------------|\n| **Talk to someone you trust** (friend, family, teacher, coworker) | Sharing lightens the load and can give you fresh perspective. |\n| **Take a short walk or do a quick physical activity** | Even 5–10 minutes of movement can reduce tension and shift your mood. |\n| **Write it out** – a journal entry, a letter to yourself, or a list of what’s bothering you | Getting thoughts onto paper can make them clearer and less overwhelming. |\n| **Practice a grounding technique** (e.g., 5–4–3–2–1 breathing, noticing five things you see, etc.) | Helps bring your focus back to the present and reduces panic. |\n| **Limit exposure to stressful media** | Constant news or social media can amplify negative feelings. |\n\n---\n\n### If you’re feeling unsafe or thinking about self‑harm\n\n- **You are not alone.** It helps to reach out right away.\n- If you’re in the U.S., you can call or text **988** (the Suicide and Crisis Lifeline).  \n- If you’re elsewhere, here are some international hotlines:\n\n| Country | Phone / Text | Website |\n|---------|--------------|---------|\n| Canada | 1‑833‑456‑4566 | https://www.988.ca/ |\n| UK | 116 123 | https://www.samaritans.org/ |\n| Australia | 13 11 14 | https://www.lifeline.org.au/ |\n| India | 91‑22‑27546669 | https://www.samaritans.in/ |\n\nYou don’t have to go through this alone. If you’re in immediate danger, please call emergency services (e.g., 911 in the U.S., 999 in the UK).\n\n---\n\n### Longer‑term support\n\n- **Therapy**: A licensed counselor or psychologist can help you work through feelings and develop coping skills.  \n- **Support groups**: Many communities (online or in‑person) offer safe spaces for sharing.  \n- **Medication**: If mood swings or depressive episodes are frequent, a mental‑health professional can discuss medication options.\n\nIf you’re willing, we can explore what kind of support might feel most helpful for you right now.\n\n---\n\n### You deserve care\n\nYou’ve taken a brave first step by reaching out, even in a short message. It shows you’re still looking for help, and that matters. Remember: feeling sad is a natural part of being human, but you don’t have to carry that weight alone. I’m here for you—tell me what you need.","annotations":[],"logprobs":null}]}],"previous_response_id":null,"model":"openai/gpt-oss-20b","reasoning":{"effort":"medium"},"max_output_tokens":null,"text":{"format":{"type":"text"}},"tools":[],"tool_choice":"auto","truncation":"disabled","metadata":{},"groq":null,"temperature":1,"top_p":1,"user":null,"service_tier":"default","background":false,"error":null,"incomplete_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":78,"input_tokens_details":{"cached_tokens":0},"output_tokens":908,"output_tokens_details":{"reasoning_tokens":191},"total_tokens":986},"parallel_tool_calls":true,"store":false,"top_logprobs":null,"max_tool_calls":null}
